      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 2.7,
      "end": 5.18,
      "text": "All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.14,
      "end": 11.16,
      "text": "For more information, or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.86,
      "end": 15.76,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.52,
      "end": 20.44,
      "text": "Aseps Fables, the Stag at the Pool.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 21.6,
      "end": 24.14,
      "text": "A thirsty Stag went down to a pool to drink.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 24.86,
      "end": 29.84,
      "text": "As he bent over the surface, he saw his own reflection in the water, and was",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 29.84,
      "end": 32.88,
      "text": "struck with admiration for his fine-spreading antlers.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 33.66,
      "end": 38.36,
      "text": "But at the same time, he felt nothing but disgust for the weakness and",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 38.36,
      "end": 39.6,
      "text": "slenderness of his legs.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 40.72,
      "end": 45.38,
      "text": "While he stood there looking at himself, he was seen and attacked by a lion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 46.06,
      "end": 51.34,
      "text": "But in the chase which ensued, he soon drew away from his pursuer, and",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 51.34,
      "end": 55.72,
      "text": "kept his lead as long as the ground over which he ran was open and free of trees.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 56.94,
      "end": 61.9,
      "text": "Becoming presently to a wood, he was caught by his antlers in the branches and",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 61.9,
      "end": 64.9,
      "text": "fell a victim to the teeth and claws of his enemy.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 65.66,
      "end": 68.52,
      "text": "Woe is me, he cried with his last breath.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 69.12,
      "end": 75.26,
      "text": "I despised my legs which might have saved my life, but I gloried in my horns, and",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 75.26,
      "end": 76.58,
      "text": "they have proved my ruin.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 77.78,
      "end": 81.4,
      "text": "What is worth most is often valued least.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 82.98,
      "end": 85.44,
      "text": "End of the Stag at the Pool",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
